div.p: GDPR Article 4(1) Raw IP is personal data uniquely identifies a natural person's device/location. Storing raw IPs without lawful basis = violation. Max fine: 20M or 4% revenue.
Salt Purpose Common IPs (e.g. 8.8.8.8) are pre-computable. Rainbow tables reverse unsalted hashes. Salt = per-deployment secret. SHA-256(ip + salt) is infeasible to invert.
